<p>King Charles III and Queen Camilla joined Pope Leo XIV for a public joint prayer in the Sistine Chapel on Thursday, marking the first time in roughly 500 years that a reigning British monarch has prayed with a pope since the 16th‑century split between Rome and the English crown [nytimes.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1][cbsnews.com#1]. The service was presented by officials as a symbolic gesture of unity between the Church of England and the Roman Catholic Church and formed a central part of the royals’ visit to the Vatican [abcnews.go.com#1][france24.com#1]. Observers said the moment carried ecumenical significance even as it unfolded amid heightened public attention to unrelated royal controversies [washingtonpost.com#1][france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/P72_GuEAG2LbVp8p2rCtJ31O23EaoWtjZm8-w8Gs-WGMn2V9pQpNjRkfXtt318UbbiogpjBGME-crilqVdcmVV0G01_6dfqsG2PMpFxOu6FHTw10z7m70RTb4LimPQclckAuCCkKW_tJEMzBTiu1eZsOMNFZUSPLzQcKP80tHbm7pQqcatm_j2T1at3SOhJg6L2OlVlsvrN8CQ' alt='Pope Leo XIV with King Charles III and Queen Camilla at the Vatican before a joint prayer service.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Ceremony atmosphere: Latin chants and English prayers echoed inside the Sistine Chapel beneath Michelangelo frescoes during the service, which coverage notes took place in front of the Last Judgment imagery [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Papal context: Pope Leo XIV, elected six months earlier and noted in coverage as the first US-born pope, led the service alongside the British monarch [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Visit timing: Charles and Camilla arrived in Rome on Wednesday for a state-level Vatican visit that included the joint worship and other diplomatic meetings [france24.com#1][abc.net.au#1].</li><li>Media context: Reporters noted the visit occurred while coverage of Prince Andrew&#x27;s ongoing scandal continued to draw public attention to the royal family [france24.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Closer ties between the two faiths as a vital “bulwark against conflict, division, and tyranny.” - King&#x27;s spokesman</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>The Vatican: The meeting was described by Vatican coverage as a gesture of unity and mutual respect between the Roman Catholic Church and the Church of England [cbsnews.com#1][france24.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/king-charles-pope-leo-pray-at-vatican-historic-first-anglican-catholic-split/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>King&#x27;s office: Royal officials framed the visit as strengthening ties between the two churches and engaging on shared moral responsibilities [france24.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251023-italy-uk-king-charles-to-meet-pope-in-display-of-unity-between-churches'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/23/king-charles-pope-leo-prayer/'>In historic moment, King Charles prays with Pope Leo at Sistine Chapel</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/british-royals-visit-vatican-historic-step-churches-respite-126786033'>British royals visit Vatican in historic step for churches</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/king-charles-pope-leo-pray-at-vatican-historic-first-anglican-catholic-split/'>King Charles and Pope Leo pray together in historic moment at Vatican</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/watch-king-charles-becomes-first-british-monarch-in-500-years-to-pray-with-pope-publicly-13944453.html'>WATCH: King Charles becomes first British monarch in 500 years to pray with Pope publicly</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/king-charles-meets-pope-leo-ahead-of-historic-prayer'>King Charles, Pope Leo pray together in a 500-year first in Vatican’s Sistine Chapel</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251023-italy-uk-king-charles-to-meet-pope-in-display-of-unity-between-churches'>Italy: UK